# Permanent-identifier allocation for https://w3id.org/qubiten/
#
# The qubiten/ space allocates one sub-prefix per Qubiten source of record.
# Two are registered:
#   mr/                — metadata registry (ISO/IEC 11179);   302 to repository docs (interim)
#   meta-architecture/ — the architecture-governance corpus;  303 content negotiation (Cool URIs)
#
# Maintainer / registration authority: Wilbye (Qubiten) <wilbye@qubiten.com>
# Allocation table + resolution modes: ./README.md
#
# Persistent, opaque PIDs (W3C Cool URIs; httpRange-14): the IRI carries the
# opaque id, never the label. Non-document IRIs answer 303 See Other.

Options +FollowSymLinks
RewriteEngine on

# ============================================================================
# mr/ — metadata registry (ISO/IEC 11179)
# Source of record: https://github.com/Qubiten/metadata-registry
# Interim target: repository documentation (superseded when the LDP
# containers provide dereferenceable resources).
# ============================================================================

# Registration authority identifier
RewriteRule ^mr/ra/qubiten$ https://github.com/Qubiten/metadata-registry/blob/main/docs/01-designation-register.md [R=302,L]

# Namespace root -> documentation index
RewriteRule ^mr/?$ https://github.com/Qubiten/metadata-registry/blob/main/docs/README.md [R=302,L]

# All other IRIs under the namespace -> repository (interim)
RewriteRule ^mr/(.*)$ https://github.com/Qubiten/metadata-registry [R=302,L]

# ============================================================================
# meta-architecture/ — architecture-governance corpus
# Source of record: https://github.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture
# 303 content negotiation per httpRange-14 (W3C "Cool URIs for the Semantic
# Web"; "Best Practice Recipes for Publishing RDF Vocabularies").
# Interim targets: the committed corpus/spine serialisations on raw GitHub,
# superseded when the platform serves dereferenceable resources directly.
# ============================================================================

# ---- corpus administered records:  /meta-architecture/id/<opaque>  ----
RewriteCond %{HTTP_ACCEPT} text/turtle [NC]
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/id/(.+)$ https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/main/docs/registry/corpus.ttl [R=303,L]
RewriteCond %{HTTP_ACCEPT} application/(ld\+)?json [NC]
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/id/(.+)$ https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/main/docs/registry/corpus.json [R=303,L]
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/id/(.+)$ https://github.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/blob/main/docs/registry/corpus.json [R=303,L]

# ---- production spine + domain:  /meta-architecture/spine/<opaque>  ----
RewriteCond %{HTTP_ACCEPT} text/turtle [NC]
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/spine/(.+)$ https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/main/production/out/spine.ttl [R=303,L]
RewriteCond %{HTTP_ACCEPT} application/(ld\+)?json [NC]
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/spine/(.+)$ https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/main/production/out/spine.json [R=303,L]
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/spine/(.+)$ https://github.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/blob/main/production/out/index.html [R=303,L]

# ---- marec: vocabulary (hash namespace):  /meta-architecture/ns[#term]  ----
# Publishing the vocabulary at its namespace IRI via content negotiation
# (swbp-vocab-pub recipe 3, hash namespace: one document carries every term).
# Interim: the vocabulary is served from the corpus graph in which its terms
# are exercised, pending a dedicated ontology serialisation (see README).
RewriteCond %{HTTP_ACCEPT} text/turtle [NC]
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/ns/?$ https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/main/docs/registry/corpus.ttl [R=303,L]
RewriteCond %{HTTP_ACCEPT} application/(ld\+)?json [NC]
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/ns/?$ https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/main/docs/registry/corpus.json [R=303,L]
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/ns/?$ https://github.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/blob/main/docs/registry/corpus.ttl [R=303,L]

# Namespace root -> the corpus reading index (interim)
RewriteRule ^meta-architecture/?$ https://github.com/Qubiten/meta-architecture/blob/main/docs/register-document-naming.md [R=302,L]
